--Objective:--
- Players aim to get as close to 20 as possible without going over.

--Setup:--
- Each player starts with one six-sided die (d10).
- Each player rolls their die to determine the first total.
- The game plays in rounds, with each round consisting of turns where players can roll or stand.

--Turn Structure:--
- On their turn, a player can either:
- Roll another d10 and add the result to their total.
- Stand, keeping their current total and ending their turn.
- If a player's total exceeds 20, they bust and are out of the round.
- Play continues clockwise until all players have either stood or busted.

--Winning:--
- The player closest to 20 without exceeding it wins the round.
- If multiple players tie, the highest single die result from their rolls determines the winner.
- If all players bust, the closest busted score (without exceeding 24) can be used as a house rule to still determine a winner.

--Optional Rules for Depth:--
- Side Deck Dice (Skill Cards Equivalent): Each player starts with 2d4s that they can roll once per round and add or subtract the result from their total.
- House Payouts: If using for in-game gambling, payouts can be 1:1 for standard wins, 2:1 for a perfect 20, and 3:1 for winning three rounds in a row.
- Tiebreaker Mechanic: If still tied, players can roll one d10 each, with the highest result winning.

Created by a coruscant local, this ale tastes sweet and is easy to drink.

A shot of liquor that is infused with a small portion of bacta. Guaranteed to get one drunk and feeling healthier at the same time.
A simple cigar. Light it up and have a puff.
A cigarette. Bad for the body bud good for the nerves.

A cider made primaly from citrus fruit gathered somewhere on viscara.
Orange with a bit of lime for those that don't want to drink alcohol but still wanna look cool. *Thumbs up*
A drink that's contents are still unknown, but when drunken, makes the consumer want to get naked and dance.

An ale created by trandoshan prisoners in a toilet on Coruscant. Now brewed professionally and sold across the galaxy but no one but trandoshans can stomach it.
A glass of high quality H20. This used to be named "Simply Pilgrim" but the bars went back to the original name of water.
